pollination.netbenefit#Definition#Result.template:
@section(Pollination/Net value of pollination services)

The map below, depicting the net value of pollination offers a general picture of the balance of supply and demand in the region of interest.

---
@figure(self, NetPollinationValue)
---

@reference(NetPollinationValue) represents the normalized surplus or deficit of pollination services in each landscape parcel. Areas in red are those where pollination services are needed but not enough provision exists to fulfill the demand. Green areas are those that can supply pollinators but there are no cultivations to benefit in the range of the pollinators. Areas in white or close to white are where there is usage and a good balance exists between provision and use.

